race.comment: BARRELLING (4) shed the maiden tag over this course and distance last time out and will have derived a stack of confidence from that breakthrough victory. Winning hoop Maloney sticks in the irons and is drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley. Can go back-to-back. ROMANTIC BUBBLE (6) couldn't have been more impressive saluting at the Gold Coast on debut before hitting the frame over this track and trip at the latest effort. Don't discount lightly. The well-related NORTH POLE (3) (half to G3 winner and G2 placed Global Quest) may have suffered from the dreaded second-up syndrome last time but the form prior was full of merit. Worth another chance. SUMMIT (12) is a last-start winner who shouldn't be discounted lightly. HOT MAJESTY (1) next in line while fresh.
